     Ok, by now just about everybody in the country has this game
from one source or the other, but a lot of people are having a
hard time figuring out what to do, so I wrote up this little
phile to help you get unstuck.  You may not want to read too far
ahead, because this tells everything you have to do in the game
and you don't want to ruin the all the fun, do you?  I heard from
some people who have the cracked version that they can't use
their orb of the moons.  This is becuase the crack removed the
doc check you have to face when you talk with Lord British right
when you start the game.  Unfortunately, right after the doc
check, is when you ask British how to use the orb and he tells
you.  This is the only way you can learn how to use it.  The
people with the cracked version can't get him to respond.  Having
the orb is really useful, but there are ways to get around it
which I will describe later.

     When you start the game, you see a nifty intro and you end
up in British's Castle.  After doing the doc check and asking
British about the orb, you can wander around and pick up anything
you want.  Make sure you get both keys (I think British gives you
one to begin with), the spell book, the magic wand (from the
mage's room), all you gear, reagents, lockpicks, etc. from your
room.  You can get the potions from the alchemy room.  Be sure to
get some cheese from the kitchen pantry.  Give the cheese to the
little mouse in the alchemy room, by the ladder.  She will join
your party.  You need her in several places later in the game. 
To get out of the castle, you need to use one of the keys to open
the gatehouses to get at the winch and lever to raise the
portcullis and lower the drawbridge.

