     Your first major task is to free the shrines.  To do this,
you need the runes.  There's one in each city.  The rune of
compassion is in Britain.  The kid in the conservatory has it,
but you have to ask her parents if it's ok if she gives it to
you.  The rune of justice is in Yew.  Get permission from the
mayor to see the prisoner.  Ask him about the rune.  He'll feed
you a story about his "6 kids to feed", but just tell him he's
lying and he'll give you the location of the rune.  The rune of
honesty is in Moonglow.  Go to Manrel (he's the dude with the
star on his forehead) and ask for the key to Beyvin's grave.  You
can get to the catacombs where Beyvin's buried through the pantry
of the tavern.  There's lots of good crud in the tombs for you to
take and the rune's in Beyvin's tomb.  The rune of honor's in
Trinsic on a pedestal in the middle of the city.  To get the rune
of humility, talk to the mayor of New Magincia.  He'll give it to
you when you tell him the name of the humblest person in town.  I
don't remember the name, but it's the one who keeps saying he's
not humble, etc.  The rune of sacrifice in Minoc is hard to get. 
You have to join the artists guild to get it.  For this you need
to learn "Stones" and make some pipes.  Go to Yew and to the
northwest, you can buy a log from the logger.  Take it to the
sawmill east of Minoc and he'll make you a board.  Julia in Minoc
can make you pipes from the board.  Gwenno, in Britain ( I think
she works at the bow place) can teach you stones.  Then the chief
artist dude will give you the rune.   In Skara Brae, the rune of
spirituality is in a basket in someone's house.  The rune of
valor is in Jhelom in a hole in the wall in a tavern.  Send the
mouse through the hole to get it. 
